HEADWORD: Brickwork
<hw>Brick"work`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Anything made of bricks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Niches in <qex>brickwork</qex> form the most difficult part of the
bricklayer's art.</q> <rj><qau>Tomlinson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of building with or laying bricks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bricky</ent>⟦br⟧
